<h2 id=3D"id-5.3-RC1ReleaseNotes-MeeteZPublishPlatform5.3">Meet eZ Publish =
Platform&nbsp;5.3</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">eZ Publish=
 Platform 5.3 is a LTS (Long term supported)&nbsp;release (see </span><a hr=
ef=3D"http://support.ez.no/Public/Service-Life" class=3D"external-link" rel=
=3D"nofollow">http://support.ez.no/Public/Service-Life</a><span style=3D"co=
lor: rgb(0,0,0);"> for supported period), </span><span style=3D"color: rgb(=
0,0,0);">it mostly offers a continuous improvement of the &quot;Platform st=
ack&quot; <span>(previously referred to as &quot;New Stack&quot;, &quot;Sym=
fony stack&quot; or &quot;6.x stack&quot;)</span> introduced with eZ Publis=
h Platform 5 in terms of features, usability and performance</span><span st=
yle=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">. </span><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><br =
/>The main topic of 5.3 has been to improve a lot in terms of integration w=
ith Symfony environment, building websites on the &quot;<em>eZ Platform</em=
>&quot; stack and continuously removing legacy dependencies. From 5.3, whil=
e it is still possible to use the legacy stack and templating system, we th=
ink using the new platform and the Symfony framework is the main way to go.=
 <span>This new platform will also be the foundation for the future eZ Plat=
form as introduced recently (previously referred as &quot;6.x&quot;) where =
it will operate standalone, without dependencies on the legacy stack.&nbsp;=
</span></span></p><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">It serves the needs=
 for both a <span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">future proofed websites on t=
op of the upcoming &quot;</span><em>eZ Platform</em><span style=3D"color: r=
gb(0,0,0);">&quot; stack, and as a stable foundation for upgrade needs for =
existing legacy (4.x) sites with support for the next 3+2 years.</span></sp=
an></p><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,=
0);">It will <span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">also be easily upgradable t=
o 5.4 which will have same legacy kernel+extensions as 5.3, is supported fo=
r the length of the 5.3 support period and provide additional features in t=
he &quot;<em>eZ Platform</em>&quot; stack for those in need for near <em>eZ=
 Platform </em>1.0 functionality, but on 5.x with it's legacy (4.x) </span>=
<span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">compatibility at the same time.</span></=
span></span></p><h4 id=3D"id-5.3-RC1ReleaseNotes-Quicklinks">Quick links</h=
4>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><a href=3D"/display/EZP/Installation=
">Install 5.3</a></span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><a href=3D"/display/EZP/Upgrading+fr=
om+5.1+to+5.3">Upgrade from 5.1 to 5.3</a></span></li>
<li><p><a href=3D"/display/EZP/Upgrading+from+5.2+to+5.3"><span class=3D"co=
nfluence-link"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Upgrade from 5.2 to 5.3</=
span><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">&nbsp;</span></span><span style=3D"=
color: rgb(0,0,0);">&nbsp;</span></a><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><br=
 /></span></p></li>
</ul></td>
