<h2 id=3D"id-5.3-RC1ReleaseNotes-5.3Features">5.3 Features</h2>
<p>5.3 introduces several new features which makes it easier to use, faster=
 to develop on and also continues to improve performance.</p>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.3-RC1ReleaseNotes-DoctrineDBAL/DoctrineBundleuse">Doctrine D=
BAL / DoctrineBundle use</h3>
<p>eZ Publish 5.3 now uses Doctrine DBAL instead of Zeta Components Databas=
e, this allows users to reuse database connection and settings with other p=
ure Symfony2 bundles which uses Doctrine ORM (default choice in Symfony2 do=
cumentation and code generators).</p>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"line-height: 1.4285715;"><a href=3D"https://github.com/e=
zsystems/ezpublish-kernel/pull/736" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow=
">DoctrineBundle integration pull-request</a></span></li>
<li><span style=3D"line-height: 1.4285715;"><a href=3D"https://github.com/e=
zsystems/ezpublish-kernel/pull/704" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow=
">Legacy storage engine refactoring pull-request</a></span></li>
<li><span style=3D"line-height: 1.4285715;"><a href=3D"https://jira.ez.no/b=
rowse/EZP-22279" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">DoctrineBundle in=
tegration issue</a><br /></span></li>
<li><span style=3D"line-height: 1.4285715;"><a href=3D"https://jira.ez.no/b=
rowse/EZP-22151" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Legacy storage en=
gine refactoring pull-request</a></span></li>
<li><a href=3D"/display/EZP/Content+Repository+configuration">Documentation=
 : Content Repository configuration</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/blob/master/do=
c/upgrade/5.3.md#database-configuration" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nof=
ollow">Upgrade documentation</a></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.3-RC1ReleaseNotes-UserauthenticationusingSymfonysecuritycomp=
onent"><span>User authentication using Symfony security component</span></h=
3>
<p><span>New login / logout functionality that uses Symfony's authenticatio=
n system, this enables any kind of login handler or SSO handler made for Sy=
mfony to also work with eZ Publish 5., including handlers for LDAP.</span><=
/p>
<ul>
<li><span><a href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/pull/691=
" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Original pull request</a><br /><=
/span></li>
<li><span><a href=3D"https://jira.ez.no/browse/EZP-22081" class=3D"external=
-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Original issue</a></span></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://confluence.ez.no/display/EZP/Authentication" class=
=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Documentation: Authentication with Symf=
ony</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"/display/EZP/How+to+authenticate+a+user+with+multiple+user+p=
roviders">Documentation: How to authenticate a user with multiple user prov=
iders</a></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.3-RC1ReleaseNotes-LegacySSOsupport"><span style=3D"color: rg=
b(0,0,0);">Legacy SSO support</span></h3>
<p>Allows use of existing legacy SSO handlers with the new user login syste=
m in 5.3 which is powered by Symfony.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/pull/691" clas=
s=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Original pull request</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://jira.ez.no/browse/EZP-22099" class=3D"external-link"=
 rel=3D"nofollow">Original issue</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"/display/EZP/Authentication#Authentication-Authenticationwit=
hLegacySSOHandlers">Documentation: Authentication with Legacy SSO Handlers<=
/a></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.3-RC1ReleaseNotes-ContentPreviewusing&quot;eZPlatform&quot;s=
tack"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);font-size: 16.0px;line-height: 1.562=
5;">Content Preview using &quot;</span><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);fon=
t-size: 16.0px;line-height: 1.5625;">eZ Platform&quot;</span><em style=3D"f=
ont-size: 16.0px;line-height: 1.5625;">&nbsp;</em><span style=3D"color: rgb=
(0,0,0);font-size: 16.0px;line-height: 1.5625;">stack</span></h3>
<p><span>With 5.3 your content previewing needs, also from the current lega=
cy based admin interface will run on the new &quot;</span><em style=3D"colo=
r: rgb(0,0,0);font-size: 16.0px;line-height: 1.5625;">eZ Platform</em>&quot=
; stack, avoiding that you need to also create all templates in legacy to b=
e able to preview correctly.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/pull/662" clas=
s=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Original pull request </a></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://jira.ez.no/browse/EZP-22051" class=3D"external-link"=
 rel=3D"nofollow">Original</a><a href=3D"https://jira.ez.no/browse/EZP-2205=
1" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow"> Issue</a></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.3-RC1ReleaseNotes-Twig&amp;TplTemplatedebuginSymfonyWebdebug=
Toolbar"><span style=3D"line-height: 1.4285715;">Twig &amp; Tpl Template de=
bug in Symfony Web debug Toolbar</span></h3>
<p><span style=3D"line-height: 1.4285715;">Developer feature known from leg=
acy which allows you to see which templates are used on a page, how many ti=
mes and how much time they spend being executed.</span></p>
<ul>
<li><a href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/pull/695" clas=
s=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Original pull request</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://jira.ez.no/browse/EZP-22152" class=3D"external-link"=
 rel=3D"nofollow">Original issue</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://doc.ez.no/eZ-Publish/User-manual/5.x/The-Website-Int=
erface/Customization-Guide/Templates-informations-in-Web-Debug-Toolbar" rel=
=3D"nofollow">Documentation : Templates informations in Web Debug Toolbar</=
a></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.3-RC1ReleaseNotes-LanguageSwitcher">Language Switcher</h3>
<p>The language switcher is built on the Symfony stack and is improved for =
a simpler usage.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/pull/834" clas=
s=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Original pull request</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://jira.ez.no/browse/EZP-22464" class=3D"external-link"=
 rel=3D"nofollow">Original issue</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"/display/EZP/Language+Switcher">Documentation : Language Swi=
tcher</a></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.3-RC1ReleaseNotes-LocationSearchAPI"><span style=3D"line-hei=
ght: 1.5;">Location Search API</span></h3>
<p><span style=3D"line-height: 1.5;">Tree based &quot;fetches&quot; are now=
 allowed be performed with the<span> new Location Search API</span>, allowi=
ng generation of tree structures much more easily by returning the location=
 instead of content, as done by existing Content Search API, and by applyin=
g any location filters on the specific location instead of <em>any</em>&nbs=
p;of the locations of a Content object.</span></p>
<ul>
<li><a href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/pull/701" clas=
s=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Original pull request</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://jira.ez.no/browse/EZP-22105" class=3D"external-link"=
 rel=3D"nofollow">Original issue</a></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.3-RC1ReleaseNotes-RESTAPIv2improvements">REST API v2 improve=
ments</h3>
<p>HTTP Cache aware, CORS support and support for OPTIONS&nbsp;method.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/pull/659" clas=
s=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Pull request for HTTP Cache aware</a>,=
 <a href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/pull/663" class=
=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Pull request for CORS support</a>, <a h=
ref=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/pull/653" class=3D"ext=
ernal-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Pull request for OPTIONS</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://jira.ez.no/browse/EZP-21044" class=3D"external-link"=
 rel=3D"nofollow">Issue for HTTP Cache aware</a>, <a href=3D"https://jira.e=
z.no/browse/EZP-21118" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Issue for C=
ORS support</a>, <a href=3D"https://jira.ez.no/browse/EZP-21044" class=3D"e=
xternal-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Issue for REST OPTIONS</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://confluence.ez.no/display/EZP52/eZ+Publish+REST+API" =
class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Documentation : REST API v2</a></l=
i>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.3-RC1ReleaseNotes-SearchAPIsupportforMapLocationCriterionand=
SortClause">Search API support for MapLocation Criterion and SortClause</h3=
>
<p>Search API is now able to search for content with geolocation making it =
possible to do geolocation range searches and sorting by distance from a po=
int; on Demo site this is shown using a restaurants-close-to-you page.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/pull/678" clas=
s=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Original pull request</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://jira.ez.no/browse/EZP-22103" class=3D"external-link"=
 rel=3D"nofollow">Original issue</a></li>
<li><p>Documentation : <a href=3D"/display/EZP/2.+Browsing%2C+finding%2C+vi=
ewing#id-2.Browsing,finding,viewing-2.Browsing,finding,viewing-Search">2. B=
rowsing, finding, viewing#2.Browsing,finding,viewing-Search</a></p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.3-RC1ReleaseNotes-Legacyextensionsinbundles">Legacy extensio=
ns in bundles</h3>
<p>With this new feature mixing legacy and &quot;eZ Platform&quot; needs ha=
s become a whole lot easier. Easily said it allows you to place legacy exte=
nsions within a Bundle structure and eZ Publish 5.3+ will make sure it is i=
njected into legacy kernel.</p>
<p>Example use case: CommentsBundle with a light admin tab in legacy allowi=
ng you to moderate comments.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/pull/719" clas=
s=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Original pull request</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://jira.ez.no/browse/EZP-22210" class=3D"external-link"=
 rel=3D"nofollow">Original issue</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"/display/EZP/Legacy+code+and+features#Legacycodeandfeatures-=
Legacybundles">Documentation : Legacy code and features - Legacybundles</a>=
</li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.3-RC1ReleaseNotes-LegacyWebsiteToolbar">Legacy Website Toolb=
ar</h3>
<p>Not to be mixed with the Web Debug Toolbar provided by Symfony and exten=
ded by eZ Publish, this feature is about allowing &quot;ezwt&quot; (Website=
 Toolbar) extension to also work in DemoBundle to provide the front-end edi=
ting functionality that you know from 4.x.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/pull/755" clas=
s=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Original pull request</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://jira.ez.no/browse/EZP-22193" class=3D"external-link"=
 rel=3D"nofollow">Original JIRA Issue</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"/display/EZP/Display+the+eZ+Website+Toolbar">Display the eZ =
Website Toolbar</a></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.3-RC1ReleaseNotes-eZFindSolr4.xsupport">eZFind Solr 4.x supp=
ort</h3>
<p>Solr 4.7.0 support in ezfind allows for use of new functionality provide=
d by Solr 4.x such as Solr Cloud allowing Solr to be scaled out over severa=
l servers, it also provides improved performance for indexing and new optio=
ns like soft commit to control this.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/pull/649" clas=
s=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Original pull request</a></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><em>Note: This feature currently has=
 several regressions, feedback wanted on how it behaves at your side.</em><=
/span></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.3-RC1ReleaseNotes-DemoSite:Places"><span style=3D"color: rgb=
(0,0,0);line-height: 1.5;">Demo Site: Places</span></h3>
<p>Taking advantage of the MapLocation feature a new feature is exposed in =
the demo showing how to implement listing and map views of content using th=
e maplocation field.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/pull/678" clas=
s=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Original pull request</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://jira.ez.no/browse/EZP-22091" class=3D"external-link"=
 rel=3D"nofollow">Original issue</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"/display/EZP/The+MapLocation+FieldType">Documentation on The=
 MapLocation FieldType</a></li>
</ul>
